This is called karma, you know?

292
00:15:08,559 --> 00:15:09,400
Who are you?

293
00:15:10,719 --> 00:15:11,159
You...

294
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:13,000
What are you saying? Why don't I understand?

295
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:13,880
No.

296
00:15:14,719 --> 00:15:16,599
Before, you'd understand me as soon as I spoke.

297
00:15:16,599 --> 00:15:17,320
Why are you now saying

298
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,760
you don't understand what I'm saying?

299
00:15:20,239 --> 00:15:21,599
How could you lose your memory?

300
00:15:22,559 --> 00:15:23,320
Do I know you two?

301
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:25,520
No.

302
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:27,479
No, you...

303
00:15:27,479 --> 00:15:28,880
You don't recognize me?

304
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,119
Are you okay?

305
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,520
Didn't the doctor say he was fine?

306
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,320
Do I know you?

307
00:15:39,159 --> 00:15:40,239
Are we very close?

308
00:15:40,679 --> 00:15:41,919
Your name is Gu Tiancheng.

309
00:15:42,119 --> 00:15:43,359
She is someone very close to you.

310
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:44,239
You don't remember her?

311
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,280
Were we very close before?

312
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,880
Why can't I remember?

313
00:15:51,799 --> 00:15:52,919
Then are we lovers?

314
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,520
Did you love me very much?

315
00:15:56,359 --> 00:15:57,520
Why do I feel

316
00:15:58,719 --> 00:16:00,599
such a familiar feeling from you?

317
00:16:01,599 --> 00:16:03,359
She treats you very well.

318
00:16:05,599 --> 00:16:06,080
No.

319
00:16:07,799 --> 00:16:08,919
Then do you know who I am?

320
00:16:09,159 --> 00:16:10,200
Do you remember who I am?

321
00:16:11,599 --> 00:16:12,679
I'm your uncle!

322
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,000
Qi Shuai, what's wrong with you?

323
00:16:14,119 --> 00:16:15,520
Why wasn't this part in the rehearsal?

324
00:16:16,359 --> 00:16:17,679
When I asked who you were,

325
00:16:17,679 --> 00:16:18,320
you were supposed to say this.

326
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,039
Where is this line?

327
00:16:19,039 --> 00:16:20,000
Why aren't you acting according to the script?

328
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:20,880
You're taking advantage of me, aren't you?

329
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:21,880
Aren't you?

330
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:22,119
No.

331
00:16:22,119 --> 00:16:22,400
Aren't you?

332
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:22,719
No.

333
00:16:22,719 --> 00:16:23,000
Aren't you?

334
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:24,919
I really didn't mean to take advantage of you, I...

335
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:35,640
You're crying.

336
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,799
Actually, I...

337
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,840
I just wanted to test...

338
00:16:40,799 --> 00:16:42,520
how important I am to you.

339
00:16:43,719 --> 00:16:44,400
So...

340
00:16:49,799 --> 00:16:50,840
please don't cry, okay?

341
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,039
I don't want to lose you again.

342
00:17:01,679 --> 00:17:03,280
Feng Ziang, let me tell you.

343
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,520
I won't let you, like last time...

344
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:06,800
get off the hook so easily.

345
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,199
What do you mean "get off the hook"?

346
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,239
Du Zheng's case was closed a long time ago.

347
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,599
The real killer is someone else.

348
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:12,719
Officer Lin,

349
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,479
you need evidence to back up your words.

350
00:17:14,479 --> 00:17:15,439
Evidence, right?

351
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:16,680
The car.

352
00:17:17,239 --> 00:17:18,239
A cloned vehicle.

353
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,079
We've already found out

354
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:22,319
that your license plate has welding marks.

355
00:17:22,599 --> 00:17:24,199
According to road traffic safety regulations,

356
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:25,880
altering a license plate number without authorization

357
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:27,079
is a serious violation of the law.

358
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:28,040
It is punishable by

359
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,119
15 days of detention,

360
00:17:29,119 --> 00:17:30,079
a 2,000 yuan fine,

361
00:17:30,359 --> 00:17:31,239
and a 12-point deduction on your license.

362
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:32,239
So?

363
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,319
So I just have to accept

364
00:17:33,319 --> 00:17:34,839
the penalty for altering a license plate,

365
00:17:34,839 --> 00:17:35,599
and that's it.

366
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:37,800
Then again,

367
00:17:38,119 --> 00:17:38,640
either

368
00:17:39,199 --> 00:17:40,560
you bring the vehicle involved in the accident here,

369
00:17:41,319 --> 00:17:41,839
or

370
00:17:42,439 --> 00:17:44,719
you show direct evidence that I killed Du Zheng.

371
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,719
Didn't you already scrap that car?

372
00:17:47,719 --> 00:17:48,839
As for whether it's scrapped or not,

373
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:50,599
you have to ask the hit-and-run driver.

374
00:17:51,079 --> 00:17:51,920
How would I know?

375
00:17:53,479 --> 00:17:54,239
Do you have evidence?

376
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,479
Who says we don't have evidence?

377
00:17:56,599 --> 00:17:57,800
After you hit Du Zheng,

378
00:17:58,199 --> 00:18:00,640
how you handled the crime scene and escaped...

379
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:02,520
Tan Feng can testify to all of this.

380
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,479
This is Tan Feng framing me

381
00:18:04,599 --> 00:18:05,400
after he committed the murder.

382
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:06,959
Then why did the witness

383
00:18:06,959 --> 00:18:08,000
only see Tan Feng's car?

384
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:09,760
Then again,

385
00:18:10,319 --> 00:18:11,359
when Du Zheng was alive,

386
00:18:11,599 --> 00:18:12,839
the one he was investigating was Tan Feng,

387
00:18:13,079 --> 00:18:13,880
not me.

388
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,199
Tan Feng is framing me.

389
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:17,319
Fine.

390
00:18:19,439 --> 00:18:20,959
Then let's just wait it out.

391
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,400
Even with only Tan Feng's testimony

392
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,839
and your cloned vehicle issue,

393
00:18:26,319 --> 00:18:27,719
we can still charge you.

394
00:18:33,119 --> 00:18:33,640
Captain Zhao,

395
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:35,640
come out with me for a moment.

396
00:18:38,439 --> 00:18:39,280
I'll leave him to you.

397
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:53,760
Tan Feng said

398
00:18:54,599 --> 00:18:56,160
after you hit Du Zheng,

399
00:18:56,439 --> 00:18:57,800
he didn't die immediately.

400
00:18:58,560 --> 00:18:59,920
So he heard everything.

401
00:19:00,719 --> 00:19:01,599
He knew

402
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:04,319
that his closest brother wanted him dead.

403
00:19:05,319 --> 00:19:06,000
Feng Ziang,

404
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:08,119
I will catch you myself

405
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:10,640
and send you to prison.

406
00:19:11,439 --> 00:19:12,040
Alright.

407
00:19:12,839 --> 00:19:13,760
Then let's see you try.

408
00:19:14,719 --> 00:19:16,119
I'd also like to see how you take what Tan Feng,

409
00:19:16,119 --> 00:19:17,760
that paranoid lunatic, said

410
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,479
and present it to a judge as testimony.

411
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:23,160
Release him.

412
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:24,839
On what grounds?

413
00:19:24,959 --> 00:19:25,880
Who gave the order?

414
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,160
Keep your voice down.

415
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:29,880
The higher-ups are taking this case very seriously now.

416
00:19:30,199 --> 00:19:32,280
So, with insufficient evidence,

417
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,199
they want us to loosen our grip a bit

418
00:19:34,199 --> 00:19:35,839
and let the suspect move freely.

419
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:37,400
In the meantime,

420
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,680
we'll gather more manpower

421
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:39,800
to collect evidence.

422
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:42,040
Until the criminal evidence is absolutely solid,

423
00:19:44,599 --> 00:19:45,760
we have to play weak.

424
00:19:46,199 --> 00:19:47,400
This is a catch-and-release tactic.

425
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,359
Pretty much.

426
00:19:49,119 --> 00:19:50,280
We didn't have enough manpower before.

427
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,599
Now,

428
00:19:51,959 --> 00:19:53,280
the big bosses have our backs.

429
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:54,880
Feng Ziang,

430
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:56,880
just you wait.

431
00:19:59,439 --> 00:20:00,239
What's wrong?

432
00:20:02,719 --> 00:20:03,479
Does it still hurt?

433
00:20:03,479 --> 00:20:04,280
It hurts, it hurts.

434
00:20:04,599 --> 00:20:05,800
Right here, here, here. It hurts so much.

435
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:06,479
Let me see.

436
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,199
Right here?

437
00:20:09,959 --> 00:20:10,880
I'll go get a doctor.

438
00:20:11,439 --> 00:20:12,119
Don't go.

439
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:13,920
If you call the doctor over,

440
00:20:14,359 --> 00:20:15,479
they'll just give me another shot.

441
00:20:17,239 --> 00:20:18,000
Alright then.

442
00:20:19,359 --> 00:20:20,920
I remember when I was little,

443
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:23,160
whenever I got a bump or scrape,

444
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,079
my dad always liked to

445
00:20:25,439 --> 00:20:26,640
rub it with his hand,

446
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:27,640
and then

447
00:20:29,119 --> 00:20:29,760
blow on it.

448
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:31,239
Then it seemed to get better.

449
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:33,479
Kiddo,

450
00:20:33,599 --> 00:20:34,680
why don't you give it a try?

451
00:20:46,239 --> 00:20:47,479
You're just acting.

452
00:20:48,119 --> 00:20:49,160
Your acting is terrible.

453
00:20:52,079 --> 00:20:53,439
Looks like you're pretty much healed.

454
00:20:53,439 --> 00:20:54,199
I'm leaving then.

455
00:20:54,199 --> 00:20:54,800
You can't leave.

456
00:20:58,439 --> 00:20:59,520
Actually, even though today

457
00:21:00,599 --> 00:21:01,839
I got hit by that thug,

458
00:21:01,839 --> 00:21:02,719
and it hurt quite a bit,

459
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,160
I'm still really happy inside.

460
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,199
Because you came back to my side.

461
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,560
Lin Jiaqi.

462
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,520
Let me tell you,

463
00:21:12,239 --> 00:21:14,119
you deserved what happened today, you know?

464
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:15,680
So from now on,

465
00:21:16,079 --> 00:21:17,079
you have to listen to me.

466
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,000
Whenever I sleep from now on,

467
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,239
you have to stay by my side.

468
00:21:29,719 --> 00:21:30,079
Then...

469
00:21:30,079 --> 00:21:31,199
Then when I wake up later,

470
00:21:31,199 --> 00:21:31,880
you have to be here too.

471
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,280
Okay.

472
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,560
When I die in the future, you have to be there too.

473
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:37,599
Don't talk nonsense.

474
00:21:39,959 --> 00:21:41,479
Do you love me very, very much?

475
00:21:46,199 --> 00:21:47,560
Are you just humoring me?

476
00:21:48,319 --> 00:21:49,439
Who's humoring you?

477
00:21:49,719 --> 00:21:50,719
Then why did you answer so quickly?

478
00:21:50,719 --> 00:21:51,359
And so simply?

479
00:21:51,599 --> 00:21:52,400
So what?

480
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:53,560
What do you want me to say to you?

481
00:21:56,079 --> 00:21:56,800
You...

482
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,520
You should say,

483
00:21:59,160 --> 00:21:59,839
"Actually..."
